[Launch4j documentation][1] for the `&lt;path&gt;` element describes the solution:

&gt; ... it is possible to use the JAVA_HOME or PATH
&gt; environment variables to search for a runtime that was installed
&gt; without adding registry keys used for searching JREs.


So just add `path` element to your `launch4j-maven-plugin` configuration:
```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;com.akathist.maven.plugins.launch4j&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;launch4j-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;2.1.2&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;executions&gt;
      &lt;execution&gt;
        ...
        &lt;configuration&gt;
          ...
          &lt;jre&gt;
            &lt;path&gt;%JAVA_HOME%;%PATH%&lt;/path&gt;
```

  [1]: https://launch4j.sourceforge.net/docs.html#Configuration_file

