I fixed the issue uncompressing the zip dependency using a maven plugin:

    &lt;build&gt;
    &lt;plugins&gt;
        &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;executions&gt;
                &lt;execution&gt;
                    &lt;id&gt;unpack-zip-artifacts&lt;/id&gt;
                    &lt;goals&gt;
                        &lt;goal&gt;unpack-dependencies&lt;/goal&gt;
                    &lt;/goals&gt;
                    &lt;phase&gt;generate-resources&lt;/phase&gt;
                    &lt;configuration&gt;
                        &lt;outputDirectory&gt;${project.build.directory}/classes/zip-resources&lt;/outputDirectory&gt;                         
                        &lt;includeTypes&gt;zip&lt;/includeTypes&gt;                            
                    &lt;/configuration&gt;
                &lt;/execution&gt;
            &lt;/executions&gt;
        &lt;/plugin&gt;
    &lt;/plugins&gt;

This makes that the content of the zip dependency is uncompressed and put into classes folder (in this case, under a folder called zip-resources), and therefore, having them in the classpath.

